An Act to promote housing cooperatives.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 40H of the General Laws is hereby amended by adding the
2 following section:-
3 Section 10.
4 There is hereby established a Massachusetts center for housing cooperatives within the
5 executive office of housing and livable communities. The Massachusetts center for housing
6 cooperatives shall provide education, conduct outreach and promote efforts to create an overall
7 environment in the commonwealth to: (i) expand and enhance cooperative resident ownership;
8 (ii) preserve the existing and increase the number of cooperatively owned properties; (iii)
9 publicize and promote the benefits of resident cooperative housing to policy makers and the
10 general public; (iv) encourage collaborative outreach efforts regarding involvement and
11 cooperative housing ownership; (v) research and evaluate cooperative housing ownership in the
12 commonwealth; (vi) showcase cooperative housing initiatives in the commonwealth; (vii)
1 of 3

13 facilitate and coordinate the sharing of existing information and resources; and (viii) provide
14 grants pursuant to this chapter. The Massachusetts center for housing cooperatives within the
15 executive office of housing and livable communities shall focus its efforts to promote housing
16 cooperatives for low to moderate income people in the commonwealth.
17 (1) The director of the Massachusetts center for housing cooperatives shall have the
18 power to hire staff, appoint any specific committee or task force and contract with consultants,
19 agents or advisors deemed necessary to further the purposes of this section.
20 (2) The director may accept gifts or grants of money or property from any source to
21 further the work of the center; provided, however, that any money received shall be deposited
22 with the state treasurer to be kept in a separate fund in the treasury to be named the
23 Massachusetts Center for Housing Cooperatives Fund dedicated to the center and for expenditure
24 without appropriation by the director of the center in accordance with the conditions of such a
25 gift or grant. Amounts remaining in the fund at the end of a fiscal year shall not revert to the
26 General Fund and shall be available for expenditure in subsequent fiscal years.
27 (3) The director shall issue rules, regulations and procedures governing the application
28 for and delivery of services which are deemed necessary for the proper performance of the duties
29 of the center.
30 (4) Annually, the director shall file a report with the clerks of the house of representatives
31 and senate, including an inventory of housing cooperatives in the state and the specific activities
32 taken by the center to support and promote the transition of traditionally structured properties to
33 a cooperative resident ownership model.
2 of 3

34 (5) The director shall be a full-time employee of the executive office of housing and
35 livable communities and shall be appointed by and report directly to the the secretary of the
36 executive office of housing and livable communities.
37 SECTION 2. The commonwealth shall appropriate $100,000,000 in fiscal year 2026 for a
38 reserve to promote housing cooperatives throughout the commonwealth for low to moderate
39 income people, including, but not limited to acquiring real estate to establish housing
40 cooperatives, preserving, rehabilitating and satisfying the capital needs of existing cooperatives
41 through programs administered by the department of housing and community development
42 directly or through 1 or more of the following: (i) Massachusetts Housing Finance Agency; (ii)
43 Massachusetts Housing Partnership; (iii) Community Economic Development Assistance
44 Corporation; and (iv) ROC USA Capital provided further, that within 180 days of the effective
45 date of this Act, the department shall submit a report to the house and senate committees on ways
46 and means and the joint committee on economic development and emerging technologies on
47 recommendations for creating and preserving housing cooperatives throughout the
48 commonwealth.
